剪ﾙ@ce8f3e35a23d38032c2db8bb12c1ca3f127045083103fdf14842c4e774226d5fﾚXTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #292'
Path: This Week in Nushell #292
Content:




Published Saturday, March 29th, 2025
So many bug fixes this week! Thanks to everyone who chipped in!
Two new Polars commands - 
``cut``
 and 
``qcut``
 for binning
And even some improvements to the VSCode Plugin from LemmusLemmus and LoicRiegel. Thank you!
壷@cf5b38076157d5614ee6af3e5f09a108f15873fa16de13e2e3bdcc8c14c92e89ﾚ･Title: title: 'This week in Nushell #292'
Path: Nushell
Content:
blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15449] added 
``parse_warnings``
 to diagnostics reports
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15443] fixed the 
``completions.external.enable``
 config option not being respected
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15403] fixed 
``ls_color``
 for 
``‾/xxx``
 symlinks
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15383] ensured 
``open``
 sets default flags when calling "from xxx" converters
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15375] fixed parser issues with comments in subexpressions of 
``let``
/
``mut``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15364] skipped 
``eval_const``
 when parsing errors are detected to avoid panics
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15374] fixed 
``flatten``
 of empty closures
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15431] introduced Polars binning commands: 
``cut``
 and 
``qcut``
.
NotTheDr01ds:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15430] ignored problematic overlapping tests for 
``SHLVL``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15428] fixed 
``clip copy``
 stripping control characters when de-ansifying
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15380] added the current exe directory to the default 
``$NU_PLUGIN_DIRS``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15264] renamed user-facing occurrences of 
``date``
 to 
``datetime``
LoicRiegel:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15429] refactored to ensure bounded ranges
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15370] fixed 
``into datetime``
 ignoring timezone with format
.
dependabot
[
bot
]
 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15419] bumped tokio from 1.43.0 to 1.44.1
.
sgvictorino 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15400] reset argument/redirection state after 
``eval_call``
 errors
.
Mrfiregem 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15379] fixed 
``path add``
 bug when given a record
.
mokurin000 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15360] added support for ACL and SELinux in 
``cd``
 permission checks
.
