壷@c89b4eac8e8c137db47c55f63d4f056eabd999efc150bf83c67aac9c48c1026bﾚ髩itle: title: 'This week in Nushell #292'
Path: VSCode Extension
Content:
LemmusLemmus:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/201] added 
``has``
 and 
``has-not``
 operators
.
added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/200] support for floats, binary, and octal literals (with underscores)
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/199] improved highlighting of bare and raw strings, and added missing units & operators
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/198] removed irrelevant 
``autoClosingPair /**``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/197] supported raw strings
.
LoicRiegel:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/195] added syntax highlighting in Markdown code blocks
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/194] added 
``CONTRIBUTING.md``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/193] fixed vulnerabilities detected by 
``npm audit``
.
